────────────────────
    │
EKS / EC2
RDS
Lambda
2.1 Create VPC

AWS Console → VPC → Create VPC

Configure:

Name: streamvault-vpc
IPv4 CIDR: 10.0.0.0/16
Tenancy: Default

Create VPC.

2.2 Create Public Subnet A

VPC → Subnets → Create Subnet

Name: public-subnet-a
AZ: ap-south-1a
CIDR: 10.0.1.0/24

Enable:

Auto Assign Public IP = Enabled
2.3 Create Public Subnet B
Name: public-subnet-b
AZ: ap-south-1b
CIDR: 10.0.2.0/24

Enable Auto Assign Public IP.

2.4 Create Private Subnet A
Name: private-subnet-a
AZ: ap-south-1a
CIDR: 10.0.10.0/24
2.5 Create Private Subnet B
Name: private-subnet-b
AZ: ap-south-1b
CIDR: 10.0.20.0/24
2.6 Create Internet Gateway

VPC → Internet Gateways

Create:

streamvault-igw

Attach it to:

streamvault-vpc
2.7 Create Public Route Table

VPC → Route Tables

Create:

streamvault-public-rt

Add route:

Destination: 0.0.0.0/0
Target: Internet Gateway

Associate:

public-subnet-a
public-subnet-b
2.8 Create NAT Gateway

VPC → NAT Gateway

Create inside:

public-subnet-a

Allocate Elastic IP.

Name:

streamvault-nat

Wait until status becomes:

Available
2.9 Create Private Route Table

Create:

streamvault-private-rt

Add route:

Destination: 0.0.0.0/0
Target: NAT Gateway

Associate:

private-subnet-a
private-subnet-b
2.10 Create Security Groups
Application Security Group
Name:
streamvault-app-sg

Inbound:

80  TCP  Anywhere
443 TCP  Anywhere
22  TCP  My IP
3000 TCP My IP

Outbound:

All Traffic
Database Security Group
Name:
streamvault-rds-sg

Inbound:

3306 MySQL
Source = streamvault-app-sg

Outbound:

All Traffic
Verify Before Continuing

You should now have:

✅ 1 VPC

✅ 2 Public Subnets

✅ 2 Private Subnets

✅ Internet Gateway

✅ NAT Gateway

✅ Public Route Table

✅ Private Route Table

✅ Application Security Group

✅ Database Security Group
